%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcarnival-royal-caribbean-private-island-resort-compared-new-review-photos-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20logistics%20startup%20is%20getting%20'buried%20in%20inbound'%20from%20brands%20after%20de%20minimis%20ended.%20It%20just%20raised%20%2418%20million.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Employees%20smile%20inside%20Portless'%20facility%20in%20Shenzhen%2C%20China%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68374565c6ad288d14821397%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPortless%20has%20a%20fulfillment%20center%20in%20Shenzhen%2C%20China.%3Cp%3EPortless%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPortless%20has%20raised%20%2418%20million%20in%20a%20Series%20A%20led%20by%20Commerce%20Ventures.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20uses%20a%20Shein-like%20model%2C%20shipping%20from%20facilities%20close%20to%20manufacturers%20in%20China%20and%20Vietnam.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPortless%20plans%20to%20expand%20into%20India%20and%20expand%20its%20supply-chain%20services.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPortless%2C%20a%20logistics%20startup%20that%20helps%20brands%20to%20offer%20quick%20shipping%2C%20has%20raised%20%2418%20million%20in%20a%20Series%20A%20funding%20round%20led%20by%20Commerce%20Ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFJ%20Labs%2C%20eGateway%20Capital%2C%20Red%20Swan%20Ventures%2C%20and%20Group%20Up%20Ventures%20also%20contributed%20to%20the%20round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPortless%20offers%20Western%20brands%20the%20chance%20to%20use%20a%20shipping%20and%20fulfillment%20model%20made%20popular%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshein-to-sell-supply-chain-technology-experts-debate-challenges-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EShein%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-delays-de-minimis-repeal-gives-shein-temu-temporary-edge-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EShein%3C%2Fa%3E%20grew%20to%20dominate%20the%20fast-fashion%20world%20by%20responding%20quickly%20to%20changing%20style%20trends%20and%20shipping%20packages%20on%20planes%20going%20directly%20to%20customers%20from%20warehouses%20in%20China.%20Products%20cross%20borders%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20days%20rather%20than%20months.%20For%20years%2C%20Shein%20did%20this%20using%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-impact-shein-temu-sales-de-minimis-uncertainty-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ede%20minimis%3C%2Fa%3E%20provision%2C%20which%20allows%20for%20the%20duty-free%20import%20of%20packages%20valued%20at%20less%20than%20%24800.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPortless%20emulates%20this%20model%20by%20shipping%20from%20its%20fulfillment%20center%20in%20Shenzhen%2C%20China%2C%20near%20where%20many%20of%20its%20customers%20manufacture%20their%20goods.%20For%20a%20while%2C%20it%20also%20used%20the%20de%20minimis%20exemption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20on%20May%202%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20ended%20de%20minimis%20shipping%20as%20part%20of%20its%20tariff%20program.%20That%20meant%20many%20companies%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-brands-reduce-tariff-costs-bonded-warehouse-de-minimis-ends-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epivot%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPortless'%20founder%20and%20CEO%2C%20Izzy%20Rosenzweig%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20had%20been%20preparing%20for%20the%20end%20of%20de%20minimis%20since%20last%20September.%20It%20raised%20its%20Series%20A%20with%20the%20understanding%20that%20de%20minimis%20would%20be%20ending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenzweig%20said%20that%20with%20tariffs%20disrupting%20global%20supply%20chains%2C%20Portless'%20pitch%20is%20resonating%20with%20many%20brands.%20By%20fulfilling%20orders%20outside%20the%20US%2C%20the%20company%20can%20help%20brands%20defer%20their%20duty%20payments%20until%20an%20order%20crosses%20the%20border%20on%20its%20way%20to%20a%20customer.%20Portless%20uses%20an%20informal%20entry%20process%20called%20Type%2011%20to%20import%20the%20goods%20to%20the%20US.%20It%20pays%20duties%20on%20behalf%20of%20its%20brand%20customers%2C%20who%20then%20pay%20Portless%20back%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20isn't%20a%20company%20in%20the%20US%20that%20isn't%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20way%20of%20doing%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenzweig%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20getting%20buried%20in%20inbound.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusinesses%20%3Cspan%3Eimpacted%20by%20tariffs%20and%20the%20end%20of%20de%20minimis%20have%20also%20explored%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-brands-reduce-tariff-costs-bonded-warehouse-de-minimis-ends-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eother%20strategies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20like%20storing%20inventory%20in%20bonded%20warehouses%20and%20foreign%20trade%20zones%2C%20to%20defer%20their%20duty%20payments%20and%20lessen%20the%20hit%20on%20their%20balance%20sheets%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Portless%20logo%20is%20shown%20inside%20its%20fulfillment%20center%20in%20Shenzhen%2C%20China%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6837470e6ffb6822ec61a769%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20look%20inside%20Portless'%20Shenzhen%20fulfillment%20center.%3Cp%3EPortless%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPortless%20typically%20works%20with%20mid-market%20brands%20earning%20between%20%245%20million%20and%20%24150%20million%20in%20annual%20revenue.%20Rosenzweig%20said%20brands%20of%20that%20size%20benefit%20the%20most%20from%20having%20better%20access%20to%20cash%2C%20which%20Portless%20helps%20with%20by%20fulfilling%20small%20orders%20by%20plane%20instead%20of%20tying%20up%2