n-homeownership-responsibility-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edefault%20milestone%20of%20adulthood%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20a%20reflection%20of%20status%20and%20security%20%E2%80%94%20a%20new%20signifier%20of%20pampered%2C%20upper-middle-class%20life.%20That%20has%20created%20a%20new%20layer%20of%20challenges%20for%20millennials%20untying%20the%20knot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%2012%20divorced%20millennials%20I%20spoke%20with%2C%20all%20but%20one%20are%20white%20and%20have%20obtained%20at%20least%20some%20college%20education%2C%20all%20but%20two%20have%20degrees%2C%20and%20most%20were%20older%20than%20the%20median%20age%20for%20first%20marriages%20in%20the%20years%20they%20tied%20the%20knot.%20Most%20were%20able%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20while%20they%20were%20married%2C%20but%20several%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-house-home-real-estate-mortgage-rates-rent-debt-boomers-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elocked%20out%20of%20the%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20post-divorce.%20Most%20had%20student%20debt.%20For%20all%20of%20them%2C%20divorce%20has%20brought%20on%20a%20significant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-big-money-mistake-holding-cash-not-buying-stocks-investing-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efinancial%20burden%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20secret%20that%20being%20single%20is%20a%20lot%20more%20expensive%20than%20sharing%20costs%20with%20another%20wage-earning%20adult.%20A%20Pew%20analysis%20of%202023%20Federal%20Reserve%20data%20found%20that%2077%25%20of%20partnered%20adults%20said%20they're%20doing%20at%20least%20OK%20financially%2C%20compared%20with%2064%25%20of%20unpartnered%20adults.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20get%20a%20divorce%2C%20they're%20cutting%20their%20net%20worth%20in%20half.%20That%20is%20going%20to%20have%20a%20drastic%20impact%20on%20their%20savings%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kristyn%20Carmichael%2C%20a%20professional%20mediator%2C%20family%20attorney%2C%20and%20Certified%20Divorce%20Financial%20Analyst%20for%20the%20Couples%20Solutions%20Center%20in%20Phoenix.%20%26quot%3BIn%20addition%20to%20that%2C%20they're%20doubling%20their%20expenses.%20Can%20they%20afford%20to%20live%20in%20the%20same%20city%3F%20Can%20they%20afford%20to%20have%20the%20same%20lifestyle%3F%20In%20a%20lot%20of%20cases%2C%20when%20they%20get%20through%20a%20divorce%2C%20the%20answer%20is%20no.%26quot%3B%20The%20couples%20with%20the%20highest%20debt%20and%20fewest%20assets%20are%20the%20ones%20with%20the%20most%20to%20lose%2C%20Carmichael%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAshley%20Claire%2C%20a%2033-year-old%20tech%20consultant%20in%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%2C%20whose%20five-year%20marriage%20ended%202%20%C2%BD%20years%20ago%2C%20says%20that%20when%20she%20began%20posting%20about%20her%20divorce%20on%20TikTok%2C%20she%20was%20stunned%20by%20the%20experiences%20others%20shared.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20shocking%20to%20see%20how%20much%20people%20are%20spending%20to%20get%20divorced%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjp-morgan-left-job-panic-no-longer-regret-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHugh%20Morris%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimates%20that%20he%20lost%20between%20%24230%2C000%20and%20%24300%2C000%20over%20the%20course%20of%20his%20divorce%20last%20year.%20A%2031-year-old%20financial%20advisor%20in%20North%20Dallas%2C%20he%20had%20been%20the%20sole%20earner%20in%20his%20marriage%2C%20which%20left%20him%20to%20cover%20legal%20fees%20for%20both%20sides%20and%20household%20bills%20while%20taking%20major%20financial%20hits%3A%20a%20%24100%2C000%20home%20sale%20loss%2C%20a%20split%20401(k)%2C%20and%20between%20%245%2C000%20and%20%2410%2C000%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcredit-card-debt-payment-interest-rates-inflation-personal-finance-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecredit%20card%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20loss%20from%20the%20divorce%20has%20been%20devastating%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BI've%20had%20to%20change%20my%20lifestyle%20%E2%80%94%20get%20cheaper%20housing%2C%20not%20eat%20out%20as%20much.%20My%20net%20worth%20is%20slowly%20recovering%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20the%20steep%20cost%20is%20deterring%20them%20from%20signing%20the%20papers%20at%20all.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20got%20a%20divorce%2C%20lawyer's%20fees%20aside%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20we%20would%20afford%20our%20own%20separate%20places%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Fask%2Fcomments%2F1gxs13z%2Fhow_do_people_afford_a_divorce%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20Reddit%20posts%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20subject%20says.%20Its%20title%20asks%20the%20question%20weighing%20on%20countless%20unhappily%20married%20millennials'%20minds%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20people%20afford%20a%20divorce%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20not%20all%20millennials%20have%20the%20assets%20to%20fund%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-had-two-divorces-maintains-important-family-connections-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebig%20divorce%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20if%20the%20courts%20assume%20they%20do.%20Piper%2C%20a%20mom%20of%20two%20now%20in%20her%20late%2030s%2C%20didn't%20work%20outside%20the%20home%20when%20she%20filed%20for%20divorce%20in%20her%20late%2020s%20(for%20the%20sake%20of%20her%20safety%2C%20she%20asks%20that%20we%20use%20a%20pseudonym).%20Apart%20from%20monthly%20%24300%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-social-security%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edisability%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20mental%20health%20condition%20that%20prevented%20her%20from%20entering%20the%20job%20market%2C%20she%20had%20no%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20unplanned%20pregnancy%20in%20her%20early%2020s%20led%20to%20her%20decision%20to%20get%20married.%20But%20after%20the%20birth%20of%20their%20second%20daughter%2C%20she%20says%2C%20her%20now-ex-husband%2C%20a%20car%20salesman%2C%20started%20drinking.%20%26quot%3BThen%20he%20started%20gambling%2C%26quot%3B%20Piper%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20racked%20up%20debt%20and%20became%20violent.%20One%20day%2C%20when%20their%20daughters%20were%20roughly%202%20and%205%2C%20she%20says%2C%20he%20punched%20a%20hole%20through%20her%20bedroom%20door%20while%20she%20and%20the%20girls%20stood%20on%20the%20other%20side.%20She%20says%20that%20he%20raised%20his%20fist%20to%20hit%20her%20and%20that%20he%20stopped%20only%20when%20he%20saw%20that%20their%20younger%20daughter%20was%20in%20her%20arms.%20Piper%20decided%20there%20and%20then%20that%20it%20was%20time%20to%20get%20out%2C%20she%20adds.%20Her%20ex's%20divorce%20lawyer%20covered%20most%20of%20the%20proceedings%2C%20which%20meant%20that%2C%20luckily%20for%20her%2C%20her%20ex%20carried%20the%20lion's%20share%20of%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20today's%20family%20court%20system%2C%20non-wage-earning%20divorce%20petitioners%20like%20Piper%20are%20especially%20vulnerable.%20Despite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-women-swearing-off-marriage-dating-single-jobs-work-education-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egender%20disparities%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20household%20earnings%20and%20who%20takes%20on%20the%20bulk%20of%20domestic%20responsibilities%20%E2%80%94%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20prevalence%20of%20financial%20abuse%20and%20deception%20%E2%80%94%20multiple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdivorce-attorney-shares-four-common-mistakes-couples-do-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edivorce%20attorneys%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20me%20that%20divorced%20millennials%20are%20navigating%20a%20system%20that%20presumes%20greater%20equality%20than%20is%20often%20actually%20the%20case.%20Though%20an%20analysis%20of%20survey%20data%20from%20between%202009%20and%202015%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.stanford.edu%2F~mrosenfe%2FRosenfeld_gender_of_breakup.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20women%20initiated%20over%20two-thirds%20of%20heterosexual%20divorces%2C%20their%20statistically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpay-gap-by-state-how-much-women-and-men-earn-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elower%20earning%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%20means%20they%20often%20have%20less%20financial%20leverage%20to%20push%20back%20against%20legal%20disputes%20from%20aggrieved%20spouses.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20custody%20battles%20and%20asset%20divisions%20are%20far%20more%20likely%20to%20get%20drawn%20out%20and%20add%20up%20in%20cost%2C%20while%20spousal%20support%20obligations%20are%20being%20granted%20far%20less%20often%20because%20of%20the%20expectation%20that%20both%20parties%20will%20independently%20be%20able%20to%20earn%20a%20living.%20Child%20support%20obligations%20are%20also%20on%20the%20decline%3A%20After%20adjusting%20for%20inflation%2C%20custodial%20parents%20received%2015%25%20less%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchild-support-doesnt-cover-all-kids-expenses-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echild%20support%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20than%20they%20had%2040%20years%20earlier%20in%201981.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacqueline%20Newman%2C%20a%20managing%20partner%20at%20the%20matrimonial%20law%20firm%20Berkman%20Bottger%20Newman%20%26amp%3B%20Schein%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20points%20out%20that%20it's%20relatively%20common%20for%20married%20people%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmotherhood-made-me-question-the-career-i-loved-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleave%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20various%20reasons%2C%20such%20as%20caring%20for%20families%20or%20dealing%20with%20a%20personal%20health%20issue.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20they%20do%20that%2C%20they%20are%20becoming%20very%20financially%20dependent%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20don't%20think%20courts%20are%20as%20sympathetic%20to%20it%20as%20they%20once%20were.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETen%20years%20out%20of%20her%20marriage%2C%20Piper%20remains%20unable%20to%20work%20because%20of%20her%20disability%20and%20lives%20in%20government-subsidized%20housing%20with%20her%20teenage%20daughters%2C%20whom%20she%20has%20full%20custody%20of.%20Between%20disability%20benefits%2C%20Supplemental%20Nutrition%20Assistance%20Program%20benefits%2C%20and%20child%20support%20payments%2C%20she%20has%20about%20%241%2C800%20every%20month%20to%20cover%20her%20rent%2C%20utilities%2C%20and%20basic%20expenses%20for%20her%20daughters.%20Fortunately%2C%20her%20parents%20and%20her%20ex-husband's%20parents%20all%20live%20nearby%20and%20chip%20in%20for%20clothes%20and%20school%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20me%20sound%20like%20a%20total%20bum%2C%20but%20I've%20made%20it%20work%20because%20my%20family%20has%20helped%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20really%20lucky%20that%20I%20have%20a%20supportive%20family%20around%20me%2C%20and%20my%20kids%20have%20people%20that%20really%2C%20really%20love%20them%20and%20care%20about%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202023%20Experian%20survey%2C%20nearly%20half%20of%20millennial%20respondents%20said%20they%20considered%20themselves%20somewhat%20or%20very%20financially%20dependent%20on%20their%20parents.%20Several%20of%20the%20women%20I%20spoke%20with%20for%20this%20story%20told%20me%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-living-at-home-relying-on-parents-safety-net-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eparental%20help%3C%2Fa%3E%20proved%20vital%20in%20helping%20them%20get%20back%20on%20their%20feet%20post-divorce%2C%20whether%20that%20meant%20rent-free%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhere-gen-zers-millennials-live-with-their-parents-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eaccommodations%20in%20the%20family%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20supplementary%20cash%2C%20or%20an%20interest-free%20loan%20to%20help%20cover%20major%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20mom%20was%20my%20safety%20net%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Crystal%20Smith%2C%20a%2040-year-old%20copywriter%20in%20San%20Antonio%20who%20got%20divorced%20in%20summer%202022.%20%26quot%3BShe%20helped%20me%20pay%20for%20my%20mortgage%20the%20first%20month%20after%20my%20divorce%20when%20I%20was%20truly%20financially%20on%20my%20own.%20I%20would%20not%20have%20been%20able%20to%20survive%20without%20at%20least%20knowing%20she%20was%20there%20to%20help%20if%20I%20needed%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20was%20also%20a%20stay-at-home%20mom%20to%20her%20two%20daughters%2C%20now%2013%20and%2015%2C%20for%20much%20of%20her%20marriage.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20have%20the%20means%20to%20leave%20a%20bad%20situation%20for%20many%20years.%20It%20wasn't%20until%20I%20happened%20to%20stumble%20into%20a%20job%20that%20paid%20a%20solid%20living%20wage%20that%20I%20even%20got%20the%20courage%20to%20jump%20and%20ask%20for%20a%20divorce%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20referring%20to%20a%20%2470%2C000%20yearly%20salary.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20hadn't%20found%20that%20job%2C%20I%20would%20still%20be%20married%20to%20this%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20the%20divorce%20itself%20isn't%20expensive%2C%20it%20adds%20to%20the%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-financial-futures-jobs-economy-money-pandemic-recession-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20barriers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firl-social-startups-combat-loneliness-among-millennials-gen-z-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eisolation%20millennials%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20faced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELacey%20Bradford%2C%2038%2C%20hit%20a%20stroke%20of%20bad%20luck%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20which%20started%20just%20after%20she%20separated%20from%20her%20husband.%20Bradford%2C%20who%20lives%20near%20Kansas%20City%2C%20Kansas%2C%20had%20already%20weathered%20one%20financial%20catastrophe%20by%20graduating%20from%20college%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20Great%20Recession.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20she%20was%20happy%20to%20land%20a%20job%20as%20a%20social%20worker%2C%20but%20the%20%2430%2C000%20salary%20simply%20wasn't%20enough%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%20She%20pivoted%20to%20selling%20cosmetics%20through%20Mary%20Kay%20and%20eventually%20ascended%20to%20the%20director%20level.%20By%20the%20time%20she%20separated%20from%20her%20husband%20in%20early%202020%2C%20she%20was%20the%20sole%20household%20earner%2C%20while%20her%20partner%20stayed%20at%20home%20with%20their%205-year-old%20son.%20Then%20came%20COVID-19%20lockdowns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20went%20from%20running%20a%20six-figure%20business%20to%20having%20nothing%2C%20moving%20into%20some%20crappy%20little%20apartment%20that%20was%20only%20%24775%20a%20month%2C%20and%20being%20on%20food%20stamps%2C%26quot%3B%20Bradford%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffeared-loneliness-after-divorce-rushed-into-relationship-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edivorce%3C%2Fa%3E%20itself%20unfolded%20about%20as%20smoothly%20as%20it%20could%20%E2%80%94%20a%20blessing%20both%20emotionally%20and%20financially.%20Her%20ex-husband%20found%20a%20good%20job%3B%20she%20gave%20him%20the%20house%20they'd%20bought%20together%2C%20which%20he%20agreed%20to%20either%20sell%20or%20refinance%20within%20three%20years%20and%20then%20give%20her%20half%20the%20equity.%20They%20split%20custody%20right%20down%20the%20middle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20even%20hire%20a%20lawyer%2C%26quot%3B%20Bradford%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20went%20up%20to%20the%20courthouse%2C%20I%20got%20the%20paperwork%2C%20filled%20it%20out%2C%20he%20signed%20it%2C%20I%20turned%20it%20in.%20It%20cost%20us%20%24265.%26quot%3B%20So%20far%2C%20her%20ex%20has%20held%20up%20his%20end%20of%20the%20bargain.%20Though%20Bradford%20is%20now%20approaching%20where%20she%20was%20prepandemic%2C%20having%20gotten%20engaged%20and%20started%20a%20life-coaching%20business%2C%20it's%20been%20a%20long%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20the%20low%20divorce%20rate%20among%20millennials%2C%20many%20of%20the%20people%20I%20spoke%20with%20hadn't%20known%20anyone%20else%20in%20their%20peer%20groups%20to%20get%20divorced.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20lonely%20place%20to%20be%2C%20when%20you're%20one%20of%20the%20first%20of%20your%20friends%20to%20get%20divorced%20while%20everyone%20you%20know%20is%20in%20their%20own%20world%2C%20having%20their%20first%20or%20second%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Claire%2C%20the%20tech%20consultant%20in%20Oregon.%20Like%20many%20young%20divorced%20people%2C%20she%20eventually%20found%20community%20on%20social%20media%2C%20but%20the%20isolation%20made%20the%20separation%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20I%20spoke%20with%20has%20zero%20regrets%20about%20their%20divorces%2C%20but%20the%20impact%20for%20many%20was%20significant.%20In%20the%20decade%20since%20Bloemhof%20ended%20her%20marriage%2C%20she's%20started%20her%20own%20PR%20firm%20and%20reconnected%20with%20an%20old%20flame%3A%20her%20first%20kiss%20from%20high%20school%2C%20a%20divorced%20dad%20with%20two%20kids%20of%20his%20own.%20They've%20since%20married%20and%20had%20a%20child%20together%2C%20raising%20a%20blended%20brood%20of%20five.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20plenty%20of%20sacrifices%20along%20the%20way.%20%26quot%3BI've%20always%20needed%20to%20live%20close%20to%20where%20I%20worked%20and%20near%20the%20girls'%20school%20%E2%80%94%20which%20meant%20paying%20a%20premium%20to%20stay%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20To%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20Bloemhof%20admits%20that%20she's%20depleted%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessi